# Level 3 - Baby Steps

### _For players new to C-Warrior_

## Level 3

_The air feels thicker than before. There must be a horde of sludge._

> **TIP:** Be careful not to die! Use `health(Warrior)` and `maxHealth(Warrior)` to keep an eye on your health, and `rest(Warrior)` to earn 10% of your max health back.

### Floor Map

```
╔═════════╗
║@ s ss s>║
╚═════════╝

@ = Warrior (20 HP)
s = Sludge (12 HP)
> = stairs
```

## Abilities

### Actions (only one per turn)

- `attack(Warrior)`: Attacks a unit in the given direction (`'forward'` by default), dealing 5 HP of damage.
- `rest(Warrior)`: Gains 10% of max health back, but does nothing more.
- `walk(Warrior)`: Moves one space in the given direction (`'forward'` by default).

### Senses

- `isEmpty(Warrior)`: Returns `1` if there exists an Object in the given direction (`'forward'` by default).
- `health(Warrior)`: Returns an integer representing your health.
- `maxHealth(Warrior)`: Returns an integer representing your maximum health.

## Next Steps

When you're done editing `Player.c`, run the `run` command again.
